definition: there's not enough time (to do sth)/it's too late (to do sth)
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: It's too late to change it now. What's done is done.
sentences.chinese: 現在再改變已經來不及了，木已成舟。

sentences.english: I'm afraid it's too late to catch the first bus.
sentences.chinese: 趕頭班車恐怕來不及了。

sentences.english: In fact, you might fall asleep immediately upon switching off the light.
sentences.chinese: 事實上，你可能還來不及關燈就已進入了夢鄉。

sentences.english: Some speakers go so fast, the audience has no time to process the information they're hearing.
sentences.chinese: 有些講者太快了，聽衆來不及消化。

sentences.english: In life we rub shoulders with some people, but it was too late to meet.
sentences.chinese: 生命中有一些人與我們擦肩了，卻來不及遇見。

sentences.english: Drinks water without enough time, the backgammon supermarket's staff then proposed looks at the pear.
sentences.chinese: 來不及喝口水，步步高超市的工作人員便提議去看梨。

sentences.english: I didn’t stop to thank her; I just seized the bread and sank my teeth in it.
sentences.chinese: 我來不及感謝她，搶過麪包就喫上了。

sentences.english: Sorry this meal isn't much, John. We didn't have time to kill the fatted calf.
sentences.chinese: 約翰，很抱歉，飯菜不多，我們來不及設宴歡迎你。

sentences.english: There wasn't even time for making a surgical entry into Herring's brain.
sentences.chinese: 甚至來不及在海嶺的腦部做一個進行外科手術的通道。

sentences.english: Little Ruthie told Father everything before Mother could shut her up.
sentences.chinese: 母親還來不及阻止小露絲，她就把什麼都告訴了父親。

sentences.english: Becasue i was afraid it's too late to apply for Germany Schengen Visa.
sentences.chinese: 因爲怕德意志共合國申根簽證來不及。

sentences.english: Without stopping to think, he darted out of the cupboard, grabbed the hen and scrambled down the beanstalk.
sentences.chinese: 來不及多想，他衝出碗廚，抓起母雞，爬下了豆莖。

sentences.english: No time to manage own mood, I have to continue working.
sentences.chinese: 來不及收拾自己的情緒，繼續埋頭工作。

sentences.english: With no time to think the yearnings gave up everything for a shot.
sentences.chinese: 來不及細想思念從此孤注一擲。

sentences.english: General Fu Rong attempted to give a counterattack, but it was too late.
sentences.chinese: 大將苻融試圖反擊卻已經來不及了。

sentences.english: If I send them now they won't be ready for tomorrow,will they?
sentences.chinese: 如果現在才送去洗，明天就來不及了，對嗎？

definition: there's still time/able to do sth in time
to overtake/to catch up with/to hurry/to rush/to try to catch (the bus etc)/to drive (cattle etc) forward/to drive (sb) away/to avail oneself of (an opportunity)/until
at once/right away/immediately/on horseback (i.e. by military force)
there is nothing to be done/one can't do anything about it
(of a person) to turn round/to face about/(of a widow) to remarry (archaic)
haven't/hasn't/doesn't exist/to not have/to not be
to be dead/not to be, or cease to exist
to say again/to put off a discussion until later/moreover/what's more/besides
